<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4947951>
        a                        fabio:Figure ;
        dc:description           "FIGURES 217–231. L. (L.) pallidulus. Male. 217, Head; 218, Pronotum; 219, Foretibia showing the row of teeth (Te) on internal margin, teeth on foretrochanter (Tte) and pad (Fos); 220, Apical half of foretibia; 221, Teeth on foretrochanter; 222, Sternum and base of abdomen showing the metasternum (Ms); 223, Hemelytron; 224, Detail of punctures of hemelytron; 225, Copulatory teeth (Cte); 226, Detail of copulatory teeth (Cte); 227, Last abdominal segments showing left paramere (LP) and copulatory teeth (Cte); 228, Detail of left paramere. Female. 229, Genitalia showing punctures (Pfg) and parietovaginal gland (PG); 230, Detail of punctures on centre of VII sternite; 231, Detail of parietovaginal gland." ;
        fabio:hasRepresentation  "https://zenodo.org/record/4947951/files/figure.png" .
